ros-jazzy-benchmark-framework (0.1.18) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * KPI visualization CLI.
    - src/visualize_kpi.py: new CLI chart generator producing publication-ready
      PNG/SVG charts from kpi.json benchmark output.
      latency_histogram: horizontal grouped bar chart of per-node mean/p50/p90
        latency, colour-coded by pipeline stage (Sensor/Perception/Planning/
        Control), with inline value labels and dual legends.
      sku_comparison: grouped bar chart comparing mean latency per node across
        multiple SKUs; p90 shown as a tick marker overlay; accepts >= 2 --kpi
        files with optional --label overrides.
      resource_utilization: horizontal bar chart of CPU utilization and thermal
        readings (cpu_mean_pct, cpu_max_pct, cpu/gpu/npu temp_c); skips
        gracefully when all fields are null (WSL2/no-sysfs environments);
        annotates throttled components with a warning marker.
      _infer_sku_label: auto-detects Intel SKU family (PTL/LNL/ARL/MTL/
        RPL-R/RPL/ADL-N/ADL/TGL/Xeon/Atom) from metadata.hardware.cpu_model
        so --label is optional for cross-SKU comparisons.
    - tests/test_visualize_kpi.py: 41 unit tests; all pass headlessly via
      the Agg matplotlib backend.
    - Makefile: visualize-kpi target with SESSION= and FORMAT= parameters.

