ros-jazzy-benchmark-framework (0.1.16) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Bag-replay benchmarking without a live robot or simulator.
    - src/bag_replay_run.sh: new script — replays any ROS 2 bag at configurable
      rate/loop count through the monitor stack; collects Level 1 and Level 2
      KPIs deterministically; supports --rate, --loop, --plot, --output-parent.
    - Makefile: bag-replay, bag-replay-plot, bag-replay-benchmark targets.
  * fast_mapping benchmark pipeline.
    - src/fastmapping_run.sh: launches fast_mapping_node + bag replay of the
      bundled spinning RGB-D bag (/opt/ros/<distro>/share/bagfiles/spinning);
      auto-detects ROS distro; stops node gracefully and waits for procedure
      table flush before analysis.
    - src/analyze_fastmapping_log.py: parses fast_mapping_node.log to extract
      per-procedure timing (wait/preprocess/octree/publish) and patches kpi.json
      in-place with throughput_hz, mean_latency_ms, jitter fields, per_node and
      pairs entries; falls back to window-based KPIs when node is killed before
      shutdown table is printed.
    - Makefile: fastmapping, fastmapping-plot, fastmapping-benchmark targets;
      FASTMAPPING_BAG points to the bundled spinning bag.
  * GPU visualization fixes.
    - src/gpu_engine_defs.py: ENGINE_CLASSES regex now matches i915 fdinfo key
      names ("copy" → Blitter, "video-enhance" → VE).
    - src/visualize_gpu.py: dynamic y-axis (no 100 % ceiling clip); new
      per-engine detail panel; MaxNLocator prevents MAXTICKS warnings at >100 %
      busy; frequency panel shows graceful fallback message when all-zero.
    - src/monitor_resources.py: supplement i915 GT frequency from sysfs
      gt_act_freq_mhz / gt_max_freq_mhz when qmassa reports 0.

