ros-jazzy-benchmark-framework (0.1.11) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Add qmassa/xe GPU monitoring support in src/monitor_resources.py:
    auto-detects active DRM driver (xe vs i915) at runtime via sysfs symlink;
    xe systems use qmassa -x (headless JSON) for per-PID engine utilisation,
    power, throttle, VRAM/SMEM, and temperature (dGPU); i915 systems continue
    to use intel_gpu_top -J; both fall back to sysfs RC6 residency on failure.
  * Add _try_qmassa_local(), _find_local_qmassa(), _detect_gpu_driver() helpers
    in src/monitor_resources.py; search ~/.cargo/bin, /usr/local/bin, etc.
  * Update src/gpu_engine_defs.py: add Compute engine class (xe ccs); extend
    Render/3D, Blitter, Video, VE regexes to match xe names (rcs, bcs, vcs,
    vecs) alongside existing i915 names.
  * Add _PmtTelemetry class to src/monitor_resources.py: reads Intel PMT binary
    sysfs interface (/sys/class/intel_pmt/telem*) to provide NPU power (W),
    junction temperature (degC), and NoC memory bandwidth (MB/s); auto-detects
    SKU via GUID (MTL, ARL, ARL-H/S, LNL, PTL, WCL); purely additive — SSH
    remote monitoring path unaffected.
  * Extend _read_sysfs_npu() to bracket its sysfs delta-sample with PMT
    pre/post reads; adds power_w, temp_c, bw_mbps, pmt_gen fields to
    npu_usage.log JSON-lines when PMT is available.
  * Extend monitor_npu() console output to show power, temperature, and BW
    when present.

