 -- ECI Maintainer <eci.maintainer@intel.com>  Mon, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

ros-jazzy-benchmark-framework (0.1.6) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Add Level 2 end-to-end pipeline KPI schema and analysis
    script to satisfy (pipeline-level KPIs).
  * Add schemas/kpi_level2_v1.json (JSON Schema Draft 2020-12) covering:
    - pipeline entry/exit topics and stage sequence
    - e2e_latency_ms: mean/p50/p90/p99/max/n (method='chained', summed from
      per-stage Level 1 representative pairs)
    - throughput_hz: bottleneck stage rate (min across stages)
    - drop_rate_pct: estimated message drop from sensor to control stage
    - bottleneck_stage: stage with highest mean latency contribution
    - stage_latency_ms: per-stage breakdown (Sensor/Perception/Planning/Control)
      with representative node, input/output topics, and sample count
    - cpu_mean_pct / cpu_max_pct (null when not collected)
    - level1_source: provenance path to source kpi.json
    - metadata: same structure as Level 1 (includes hardware fields)
  * Add src/analyze_pipeline_latency.py: reads Level 1 kpi.json and writes
    kpi_level2.json, validated against schemas/kpi_level2_v1.json via
    jsonschema Draft202012Validator; auto-discovers most-recent session
    when --kpi is not specified.
  * Add quickstart option 4→6 'Level 2 pipeline KPI' to run the above
    analysis on the most recent wandering session's kpi.json.

 -- ECI Maintainer <eci.maintainer@intel.com>  Thu, 24 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

ros-jazzy-benchmark-framework (0.1.5) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Fix timestamp accuracy in ros2_graph_monitor.py: replace time.time()
    (monitor wall-clock, adds DDS transport + Python GIL jitter) with
    msg.header.stamp (publisher's own clock at publish time) for all
    messages that carry a std_msgs/Header. For headerless messages
    (e.g. geometry_msgs/Twist cmd_vel) fall back to self.get_clock().now()
    which respects use_sim_time and keeps all timestamps on the same
    time base. Add monotonicity guard to reject negative inter-message
    intervals caused by non-monotonic sim-clock jumps.
  * Add --use-sim-time flag to ros2_graph_monitor.py and monitor_stack.py.
    Auto-detect simulation mode at startup from /clock topic presence;
    flag only needed to force early enablement before auto-detection fires.
  * Pass --use-sim-time explicitly from wandering_run.sh and
    picknplace_run.sh (Gazebo sim always runs with /clock).
  * Add framework_version, ros_distro, and hardware (cpu_model, cpu_cores,
    gpu_model, total_ram_gb) to kpi.json metadata block; schema updated to require these fields and validate their structure.
    framework_version read from pyproject.toml via importlib.metadata;
    ros_distro from ROS_DISTRO env; hardware collected via /proc/cpuinfo,
    os.cpu_count(), lspci, and psutil.

